Enum StreamType

    An enum representing the stream type of a StreamInfo extracted by a StreamExtractor.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NONE

        public static final StreamType NONE
        Placeholder to check if the stream type was checked or not. It doesn't make sense to use this enum constant outside of the extractor as it will never be returned by an Extractor and is only used internally.

      • VIDEO_STREAM

        public static final StreamType VIDEO_STREAM
        A normal video stream, usually with audio. Note that the StreamInfo can also provide audio-only AudioStreams in addition to video or video-only VideoStreams.

      • AUDIO_STREAM

        public static final StreamType AUDIO_STREAM
        An audio-only stream. There should be no VideoStreams available! In order to prevent unexpected behaviors, when StreamExtractors return this stream type, they should ensure that no video stream is returned in StreamExtractor.getVideoStreams() and StreamExtractor.getVideoOnlyStreams().

      • LIVE_STREAM

        public static final StreamType LIVE_STREAM
        A video live stream, usually with audio. Note that the StreamInfo can also provide audio-only AudioStreams in addition to video or video-only VideoStreams.

      • AUDIO_LIVE_STREAM

        public static final StreamType AUDIO_LIVE_STREAM
        An audio-only live stream. There should be no VideoStreams available! In order to prevent unexpected behaviors, when StreamExtractors return this stream type, they should ensure that no video stream is returned in StreamExtractor.getVideoStreams() and StreamExtractor.getVideoOnlyStreams().

      • POST_LIVE_STREAM

        public static final StreamType POST_LIVE_STREAM
        A video live stream that has just ended but has not yet been encoded into a normal video stream. Note that the StreamInfo can also provide audio-only AudioStreams in addition to video or video-only VideoStreams.

        Note that most of the content of an ended live video (or audio) may be extracted as regular video contents (or regular audio contents) later, because the service may encode them again later as normal video/audio streams. That's the case on YouTube, for example.

      • POST_LIVE_AUDIO_STREAM

        public static final StreamType POST_LIVE_AUDIO_STREAM
        An audio live stream that has just ended but has not yet been encoded into a normal audio stream. There should be no VideoStreams available! In order to prevent unexpected behaviors, when StreamExtractors return this stream type, they should ensure that no video stream is returned in StreamExtractor.getVideoStreams() and StreamExtractor.getVideoOnlyStreams().

        Note that most of ended live audio streams extracted with this value are processed as regular audio streams later, because the service may encode them again later.
